      "writtenOn": "2020-10-23T20:39:52Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Why is there `name` and also `nameString`? \n\nI\u0027m getting the impression it\u0027s to avoid copying a string if we have a StringFragment we can use instead, but I\u0027m not sure this is actually a good optimization for the general case.\n\nsizeof(std::string) \u003d\u003d 32.\nsizeof(std::string) + sizeof(StringFragment) \u003d\u003d 48.\nstd::strings have a built-in no-malloc capacity of 15 before they actually go to allocate any storage. (This seems to be true in both gcc and clang.)\n\nHow many types will exceed 15 chars?\nI think we might be better off optimizing for a smaller IRNode and a simpler type.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 287,
        "startChar": 17,
        "endLine": 287,
        "endChar": 56
      },
      "revId": "9e582622ec97f457c04763527ea56501569864ec",
